    "faq_updated_kjbyB3": {
      "type": "faq-updated",
      "blocks": {
        "faq_item_PNmVFK": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "disabled": true,
          "settings": {
            "question": "Everything you want to know about CO₂ laser resurfacing.",
            "answer": "<p><strong>The Science of Fractional CO2</strong><br/>We utilize advanced <strong>Fractional CO2 Laser technology</strong>, widely considered the \"Gold Standard\" in dermatology for treating textured acne scars and deep wrinkles. Unlike older lasers that burn the entire skin surface, our technology creates thousands of microscopic thermal channels deep into the dermis. This triggers the body’s natural healing response, stimulating massive collagen production to \"fill in\" scars and smooth texture from the inside out.</p><p><strong>One Laser. Three Intensities.</strong><br/>We customize the depth of the CO2 energy to match your skin concerns and downtime availability:<br/></p><ul><li><strong>Level 1: The 'Refresh' (Light)Best For:</strong> Sun damage, uneven tone, and open pores.<strong>Downtime:</strong> 3-4 days (Redness and mild dryness).<br/></li><li><strong>Level 2: The 'Resurface' (Medium)Best For:</strong> Fine lines, crepey skin, and mild atrophic scarring.<strong>Downtime:</strong> 5-7 days (Bronzing and peeling).<br/></li><li><strong>Level 3: The 'Scar Repair' (Deep)Best For:</strong> Deep rolling acne scars, boxcar scars, and surgical scar revision.<strong>Downtime:</strong> 7-10+ days (Requires social downtime for maximum results).</li></ul>"
          }
        },
        "faq_item_MTQ7HM": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What skin concerns can CO₂ laser resurfacing treat?",
            "answer": "<p>CO₂ laser resurfacing is a versatile treatment that can address multiple skin concerns in a single procedure. It works by removing damaged surface layers of skin while stimulating collagen production deeper within the dermis.</p><p>It can help improve:</p><p>• Fine lines and deeper wrinkles</p><p>• Sun damage and pigmentation irregularities</p><p>• Acne scarring and surgical scars</p><p>• Enlarged pores</p><p>• Uneven skin tone and texture</p><p>• Crepey or thinning skin</p><p>• Stretch marks (in selected areas)</p><p>• Age spots and sun spots</p><p>• Skin laxity in mild to moderate cases</p><p>During your consultation, we assess your skin type, concerns, and downtime tolerance to determine whether CO₂ is the most appropriate treatment for you.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_item_HrxNLf": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Is CO₂ laser resurfacing painful?",
            "answer": "<p>A topical anaesthetic is applied before treatment to minimise discomfort. Most clients describe the sensation as heat and pressure rather than sharp pain.</p><p>Treatment intensity can be adjusted depending on your goals and downtime tolerance.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_item_ddfEcQ": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What level of downtime should I expect?",
            "answer": "<p>Downtime depends on treatment intensity:</p><p>• Light resurfacing: 3–5 days redness and mild peeling</p><p>• Moderate resurfacing: 5–7 days redness and flaking</p><p>• Deep resurfacing: 7–10+ days visible peeling and recovery</p><p>We tailor depth based on your goals and your ability to accommodate downtime.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_item_cYExH8": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How many sessions will I need?",
            "answer": "<p>Many clients achieve significant improvement from one well-planned session.</p><p>However, deeper scarring or advanced ageing concerns may require a structured treatment plan.</p><p>Your consultation determines the correct approach.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_item_UbaFJR": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "When will I see results?",
            "answer": "<p>Initial smoothing appears once healing completes.</p><p>Collagen remodelling continues for 8–12 weeks after treatment, with progressive improvements in texture, tone, and firmness.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_item_qJVU4c": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Is CO₂ resurfacing safe for my skin type?",
            "answer": "<p>CO₂ is best suited for lighter to medium skin tones.</p><p>A full assessment is carried out before treatment to ensure suitability and minimise risks.</p><p>We never proceed without confirming safety.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_item_yVNnp8": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Can I wear makeup after treatment?",
            "answer": "<p>Makeup can usually be applied once the skin surface has fully healed, typically 5–7 days depending on depth.</p><p>Aftercare guidance is provided to ensure optimal healing.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_item_Ek4P3d": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What is the difference between \"Full Face\" and \"Half Face\"?",
            "answer": "<p>Full Face treats the entire facial surface.</p><p>Half Face targets a specific area of concern, such as:</p><p>• Lower face</p><p>• Cheeks</p><p>• Perioral lines</p><p>• Forehead</p><p>The approach is customised depending on your primary concern.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_item_hcEF7D": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How long do results last?",
            "answer": "<p>CO₂ stimulates deep collagen renewal.</p><p>Results can last several years, depending on:</p><p>• Age</p><p>• Lifestyle</p><p>• Skincare</p><p>• Sun exposure</p><p>Maintenance treatments may be recommended to preserve results.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_item_x7jNzt": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Who is CO₂ resurfacing best for?",
            "answer": "<p>CO₂ may be ideal if you have:</p><p>• Acne scarring</p><p>• Deep lines</p><p>• Texture irregularities</p><p>• Sun damage</p><p>• Skin laxity</p><p>It may not be suitable if you require zero downtime or have certain medical contraindications.</p><p></p><h3></h3>"
          }
        },
        "faq_item_QwXbyn": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What happens at my consultation?",
            "answer": "<p>Your consultation includes:</p><p>• Skin assessment</p><p>• Downtime discussion</p><p>• Depth planning (light, moderate, deep)</p><p>• Clear pricing</p><p>• Aftercare planning</p><p>You’ll leave knowing exactly what recovery involves.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_item_3LC6wb": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What payment options do you offer?",
            "answer": "<p>We offer flexible payment options to make your treatment as convenient as possible. You can choose to pay per single session or pay in full for a course of treatments for better overall value. We accept card, cash, and bank transfer in clinic.</p><p>For added flexibility, we also offer 0% finance through Klarna, allowing you to spread the cost into manageable instalments with a range of payment options available, subject to eligibility.</p><p><br/></p><p>If you’re unsure which option is best for you, our team will be happy to guide you</p>"
          }
        }
      },
